<link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CEDACC;ef6b03fd.1406</link>   <description> Hello All,<br><br>The CEDA file compliance checking package, CEDA CC, has been upgraded with improved installation options and directory structure.<br><br>It can now be installed in your python system libraries with:<br>pip install ceda-cc (N.B. root access probably needed)<br>Or in your ~/bin directory with:<br>svn co http://proj.badc.rl.ac.uk/svn/exarch/CCCC/tags/1.0<br>bash userinst.sh<br>Further installation details at http://proj.badc.rl.ac.uk/exarch/wiki/PackageCedaccInstall<br><br>The usage is changed slightly: instead of invoking the command with &quot;python c4.py &lt;options&gt;&quot;, it should now be run with &quot;ceda_cc &lt;options&gt;&quot;. The options are unchanged. With this change it is easier to keep output files separate from the source and configuration files. [...]    </description>   <dc:date>2014-06-30T13:49:31+00:00</dc:date>   <dc:creator>Martin Juckes</dc:creator>   <dc:identifier>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CEDACC;ef6b03fd.1406</dc:identifier> </item>  <item rdf:about="https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CEDACC;4bf96ba2.1406">   <title>Welcome to the CEDA Compliance Checker email list. </title>   <link>https://www.jiscmail.ac.uk:443/cgi-bin/webadmin?A2=CEDACC;4bf96ba2.1406</link>   <description> Hello All,<br><br>Welcome to this new email list for the CEDA Compliance Checker software package. You are on this list because you have either used the package within CEDA or expressed an interest in using it outside CEDA, under the earlier name of &quot;CCCC&quot;, for running tests on CORDEX, SPECS or CCMI data files.
